Attempt to fetch the source .3mf from the sandbox.

$ curl -sIL --max-time 10 -A "Mozilla/5.0 ..." \
    https://makerworld.com/en/models/1348327-small-multicolor-ams-test-coin

HTTP/2 403
x-deny-reason: host_not_allowed
content-length: 21
content-type: text/plain

Conclusion: MakerWorld is on the sandbox egress denylist (host_not_allowed
is the sandbox's response, not MakerWorld's anti-bot). This is expected
and not a MakerWorld block per se — even a fresh User-Agent and a real
session cookie wouldn't get through because the request never leaves
the sandbox. Jacob downloads manually in a browser. See README Step A.
